FBIS3-1327 "drafr058_d_94007" FBIS-AFR-94-058 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Mar 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Mozambique Training for Infantry Troops Could Begin 4 Apr MB2403174194 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 1500 GMT 24 Mar 94 MB2403174194 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] The training of infantry troops for the future Mozambique Defense Armed Forces is expected to begin on 4 April. Radio Mozambique learned this from Aldo Ajello, special representative of the UN secretary general in Mozambique. Aldo Ajello said military uniforms for the infantry troops have already arrived at the South African port of Durban and are expected to arrive in the country soon.
